This paper is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category as it deals with medium access control (MAC) scheduling in wireless networks. It may also belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) category as it considers the impact of channel conditions on throughput. The paper also involves system-level analysis and optimization, which could place it in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category. Additionally, the paper specifically focuses on MAC scheduling algorithms, which could place it in the Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) category. Finally, the paper involves performance analysis and optimization, which could place it in the Performance (cs.PF) category.
